 started also developing empirical research in this area, with close attention to the role of expert knowledge and technology in financial activities.</p>

</sec>
<sec>
<st>
Main topics</st>
<p>

Research topics in social studies of finance include the cultural world and work habits of <link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../542/4788542.xml">
traders</link> and other professionals in financial markets, the <link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../313/46313.xml">
globalization</link> and <link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../149/153149.xml">
regulation</link> of financial services, the processes of <link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../450/118450.xml">
innovation</link> in the financial industry and the problems of <link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../617/25617.xml">
risk</link> and <link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../778/63778.xml">
uncertainty</link> that characterize such processes.</p>

